narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I'd recommend, with the caveat that the class is most worth taking if you feel after the first few classes that the material could be interesting to you and that the added class time will benefit your learning.
It's okay, but not the best

The course is intended for students with zero to limited experience with calculus. I would recommend this course to everyone who fits this description and is interested in economics or looking for an interesting course. This is a GREAT class!
A economics seminar, so more difficult than a lecture.
